CAPE Town City FC have confirmed that Mpho Makola has exteded his stay with the club. ontract extension until the end of the 2021-22 season. Makola joined The Citizens on a free transfer in 2019 after seven years at Soweto giants Orlando Pirates. Makola’s experience and composure has proved to be invaluable in the dressing room, especially among the club’s younger players. “The club is delighted to have signed a new contract with Mpho Makola. Our midfield general extends his stay until June 2022,” a Cape Town City statement read on social media. Mpho Makola has made 52 appearances for Cape Town City, scoring two goals and registering three assists. The club is delighted to have signed a new contract with Mpho Makola. Our midfield general is extends his stay until June 2022! To more class in the midfield ?? #iamCityFC pic.twitter.com/NGL06HU6NS 